  • Method Details

    • addAirline

      public abstract int addAirline​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String alias, java.lang.String iata, java.lang.String icao, java.lang.String callsign, java.lang.String country, java.lang.String active)
      Ensures validity of parameters, passes them into the saveAirline method of AirlineService.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the airline, cannot be null.
      alias - The alias of the airline.
      iata - The 2-letter IATA code of the airline, must be unique, may be null if not known/assigned.
      icao - The 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, must be unique, may be null if not known/assigned.
      callsign - The callsign of the airline.
      country - The country of the airline.
      active - "Y" if the airline is or has until recently been operational, "N" if it is defunct, cannot be null.
      Returns:
      int The airline_id of the new airline that has been created by AirlineService.

    • addAirport

      public abstract int addAirport​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String city, java.lang.String country, java.lang.String iata, java.lang.String icao, java.lang.String latitude, java.lang.String longitude, java.lang.String altitude, java.lang.String timezone, java.lang.String dst, java.lang.String tz)
      Ensures validity of parameters, passes them into the saveAirport method of AirportService.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the airport, cannot be null.
      city - The city of the airport, cannot be null.
      country - The country of the airport, cannot be null.
      iata - The 3-letter IATA code of the airport, must be unique, may be null if not known/assigned.
      icao - The 4-letter ICAO code of the airport, must be unique, may be null if not known/assigned.
      latitude - The latitude of the airport, a string. Negative is South, positive is North, cannot be null.
      longitude - The longitude of the airport, a string. Negative is West, positive is East, cannot be null.
      altitude - The altitude of the airport in feet, a string. Cannot be null.
      timezone - The hours offset from UTC, a string, cannot be null.
      dst - The daylight savings time of the airport, one of E (Europe), A (US/Canada), S (South America), O (Australia), Z (New Zealand), N (None) or U (Unknown), cannot be null.
      tz - Timezone in "tz" (Olson) format, i.e. Country/Region. Cannot be null.
      Returns:
      int The airport_id of the new airport that has been created by AirportService.

    • addFlightEntry

      public abstract int addFlightEntry​(int flightID, java.lang.String locationType, java.lang.String location, java.lang.String altitude, java.lang.String latitude, java.lang.String longitude)
      Ensures validity of parameters, passes them into the saveFlight method of FlightService.
      Parameters:
      flightID - The integer flight_id of the new flight entry, cannot be null.
      locationType - The location type of the flight entry location, one of "APT", "VOR", or "FIX", cannot be null.
      location - The location of the flight entry, cannot be null.
      altitude - The altitude of the plane at the time of the flight entry, in feet. A string, cannot be null.
      latitude - The latitude of the plane at the time of the flight entry, a string. Negative is South, positive is North, cannot be null.
      longitude - The longitude of the plane at the time of the flight entry, a string. Negative is West, positive is East, cannot be null.
      Returns:
      int The unique id of the new flight entry that has been created by FlightService.

    • addRoute

      public abstract int addRoute​(java.lang.String airline, java.lang.String sourceAirport, java.lang.String destAirport, java.lang.String codeshare, java.lang.String stops, java.lang.String equipment)
      Ensures validity of parameters, passes them into the saveRoute method of RouteService.
      Parameters:
      airline - The 2-letter IATA code or 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, cannot be null.
      sourceAirport - The 3-letter IATA code or 4-letter ICAO code of the source airport, cannot be null.
      destAirport - The 3-letter IATA code or 4-letter ICAO code of the destination airport, cannot be null.
      codeshare - "Y" if the flight is operated by a different airline, otherwise "N". Cannot be null.
      stops - The number of stops for the flight, 0 if it is direct. A string, cannot be null.
      equipment - 3-letter codes for plane types(s) commonly used for this flight, separated by spaces. Cannot be null.
      Returns:
      int The route_id of the new route that has been created by RouteService.
